{"key":"post-18958198","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>18958198</id>\n<content>The problem is that &lt;i&gt;evaporation of moisture&lt;/i&gt; is a major pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; Anything which slows down evaporation impedes this process.&amp;nbsp; We get best results from an ebb and flow of substrate/casing moisture levels, and these crystals tend to cause a steady-state moisture level.&amp;nbsp; That's good in plants, bad in mushroom growing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To obtain best performance in mushroom growing, we mist to hydrate the substrate or casing layer, and then let it start to dry out again before re-misting.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>18962442</next>\n<prev>18958161</prev>\n<first>18957552</first>\n<last>18962442</last>\n<when>1381411689</when>\n<utime>10/10/13 04:28 PM</utime>\n</post>"}